ğŸ”¹ Problem Samajhna

Hume triplets = [[a,b,c], ...] diye gaye hain.Hume target = [x,y,z] banana hai.
Operation allowed:
Do triplets i aur j uthao aur triplets[j] = [max(ai, aj), max(bi, bj), max(ci, cj)] bana do.
Matlab hum merge karke har coordinate ka maximum le sakte hain. Ye operation multiple times kar sakte hain.
Goal: Check karo ki kya target = [x,y,z] kisi triplet me ban sakta hai.

ğŸ”¹ Key Observation
ğŸ‘‰ Operation sirf maximum le raha hai.
Matlab koi bhi coordinate kabhi chhota nahi hoga, sirf same ya bada hoga.
Toh agar target banana hai, hume aise triplets chahiye jisme:
Pehle coordinate me x ho aur wo y aur z se bada na ho
Dusre coordinate me y ho aur wo x aur z se bada na ho
Teesre coordinate me z ho aur wo x aur y se bada na ho

Matlab: Har coordinate ke liye at least ek triplet hona chahiye jo us coordinate ko exactly match karta ho aur baaki coordinates target se exceed na kare.
Agar ye teeno conditions puri hoti hain â†’ target ban jaayega.

ğŸ”¹ Approach
Har triplet [a,b,c] iterate karo.
Agar koi coordinate target se bada hai (jaise a > x ya b > y ya c > z) â†’ is triplet ko ignore karo (useless hai, kyunki merge karke hamara target exceed ho jaayega).
Agar koi valid triplet hai:
Agar a == x â†’ x coordinate cover ho gaya.
Agar b == y â†’ y coordinate cover ho gaya.
Agar c == z â†’ z coordinate cover ho gaya.
Agar teeno cover ho gaye â†’ return true.
Warna loop ke baad false.

Example 1:
triplets = [[2,5,3],[1,8,4],[1,7,5]]
target = [2,7,5]

[2,5,3] â†’ valid (sab target se â‰¤)
has x = 2 âœ…
[1,8,4] â†’ skip (8 > 7) âŒ
[1,7,5] â†’ valid
has y = 7 âœ…
has z = 5 âœ…
â†’x,y,z teeno mil gaye â†’ return true âœ…

Example 2:
triplets = [[3,4,5],[4,5,6]]
target = [3,2,5]
[3,4,5] â†’ skip (4 > 2) âŒ
[4,5,6] â†’ skip (4 > 3, 5 > 2, 6 > 5) âŒ
Koi valid triplet nahi â†’ false âœ…

Example 3:
triplets = [[2,5,3],[2,3,4],[1,2,5],[5,2,3]]
target = [5,5,5]
[2,5,3] â†’ valid, has y=5
[2,3,4] â†’ valid
[1,2,5] â†’ valid, has z=5
[5,2,3] â†’ valid, has x=5
x=5, y=5, z=5 sab cover ho gaye â†’ true âœ…

TC = O(N)
SC = O(1) 

class Solution {
public:
    bool mergeTriplets(vector<vector<int>>& triplets, vector<int>& target) {

        int x = target[0], y = target[1], z= target[2];
        bool cx = false, cy= false, cz=false;

        for(auto &t : triplets){
            int a = t[0], b = t[1], c = t[2];
            // discard if any value > target
            if(a > x || b > y || c > z){
                continue;
            }
            if(a == x) cx = true;
            if(b == y) cy = true;
            if(c == z) cz = true;

            if(cx && cy && cz){
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
